-- "Personalized items" is ambiguous, so we search in title and abstract
-- for phrases related to personalization and items/recommendations.

    p.paper_id,
    p.title,
    p.abstract,
    p.venue,
    p.year,
    p.citation_count,
    p.open_access_url

        p.title ILIKE '%personalisation%' OR
        p.title ILIKE '%personalization%' OR
        p.abstract ILIKE '%personalized%' OR
        p.abstract ILIKE '%personalisation%' OR
        p.abstract ILIKE '%personalization%'

        p.abstract ILIKE '%item%' OR
        p.abstract ILIKE '%items%' OR
        p.abstract ILIKE '%recommendation%' OR

-- Example: find relevant papers for a given topic and (optionally) author
-- Replace :topic and :author_name with your search terms

SELECT
    p.paper_id,
    p.title,
    p.abstract,
    p.venue,
    p.year,
    p.citation_count,
    p.open_access_url,
    array_agg(a.name ORDER BY pa.author_position) AS authors
FROM Papers AS p
LEFT JOIN PaperAuthors AS pa ON pa.paper_id = p.paper_id
LEFT JOIN Authors AS a       ON a.author_id = pa.author_id
WHERE
    -- Topic / keyword relevance in title or abstract
    (
        p.title    ILIKE '%' || :topic || '%'
        OR p.abstract ILIKE '%' || :topic || '%'
    )
    -- Optional: filter by author name (comment out if not needed)
    AND (
        :author_name IS NULL
        OR a.name ILIKE '%' || :author_name || '%'
    )
GROUP BY
    p.paper_id,
    p.title,
    p.abstract,
